														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866443">
									

<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> SCP Article<br />
<strong>Genre :</strong> horror/emotional, but not terribly dramatic in either category</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> a pound of flesh, maybe a little less, that is upset to be alive and unaccompanied.</p>
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> A small cube of seemingly human flesh is found in a hospital scheduled for demolition. Even experienced agents can sometimes overlook small details, to dangerous affect.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> The cube itself is an abnormality, but the liquid it produces could provide a springboard for other SCPs that need a particular corrosive liquid, something i've seen in a couple other premises. Additionally, it is relatively simple but captures the sort of grotesque nature of some of the Safe objects that I really love to see in an SCP myself.</p>
<p><strong>Additional Notes:</strong> I don't have anything of particular worry but I am excited for folks to take a look! I have my sandbox ready to go whenever someone wants to take a look.</p>

							</div>

								
					
