																	<a href="/forum/t-13973726/requesting-greenlight-for-scp-your-chance-to-win#post-4866434">Re: Requesting Greenlight for SCP (Your Chance to Win)</a>
									</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=455145&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610247952" alt="Petrograd" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=455145)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/petrograd" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(455145); return false;" >Petrograd</a></span> <span class="odate time_1610244496 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Jan 2021 02:08</span>
																	<br/>
						in discussion <a href="/forum/c-89000/help:ideas-critique">Writing Help / Help: Ideas Critique</a> &raquo;
						<a href="/forum/t-13973726/requesting-greenlight-for-scp-your-chance-to-win">Requesting Greenlight for SCP (Your Chance to Win)</a>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4866434">
									

<p>All-in-all, this seems really predictable. It really just operates like a normal quiz show, outside of the petty vandalism. The anomalies don't add anything interesting to that baseline.</p>
<p>With these kind of SCPs, it can often help to think about the &quot;personality&quot; of the SCP, or at least what it &quot;wants.&quot; On this read-through, it looks like they just want to run a normal quiz show. You could dig further into that, push what this being/operation <em>is</em>, what they <em>want</em>, and how they <em>try to get it</em>. There are a lot of directions you could go from there (making them sympathetic, making them really alien, etc.), but it'll take a lot of further development for this to go anywhere.</p>
<p>Compare this to something like <a href="/scp-2030">SCP-2030</a>, which only has the basic form of a TV show. (There's a really good breakdown of what makes SCP-2030 unique and effective <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/forum/t-4309163/what-makes-a-heavily-disturbing-scp-great#post-3635568">in this post</a>)</p>

							</div>

								
					
