<p>The sites are based on language, not nationality. English-speaking Canadian users would be most at home on -EN, while primarily-French-speaking Canadians would likely be more comfortable on -FR. There is absolutely no reason to institute a &quot;Canadian Branch&quot; when the major official languages<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-556428-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-556428-1')">1</a></sup> are covered already.</p>
<p>There is nothing stopping someone from writing Canada-based content here, on -FR, or, indeed, on literally any of the wikis.</p>
