<p>Warning, there might be potentially triggering content here. I'm an amateur writer so I don't know if I can handle these topics very well yet.</p>
<p><strong>Seeking Greenlights:</strong> Yes</p>
<p><strong>Page Type:</strong> Tale</p>
<p><strong>Genre (Optional):</strong> Drama/Emotional</p>
<p><strong>Page Layout (Optional):</strong> Typical story structure (maybe a choose your own adventure short?)</p>
<p><strong>Elevator Pitch:</strong> end of the world scenario, 2 people survive, one of them decides that living in an empty world of just pain isn't worth it and decides to end their own life. The second person after living with the other for so long is crushed by this and either goes to recover from this trauma or is impacted by this so heavily that she loses the will to go on.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p><strong>Central Narrative:</strong> GD-Class Gestalt Dissolution Scenario occurs</p>
<p>90% of the population vulnerable without a specific immunity gene is turned into eldritch primal hunters, extremely dangerous with varying anomalous effects ranging from instantly causing simulated 3rd degree burns to resurrecting the dead as mindless slaves. All of which with diminished intelligence and fight each other regularly in tribe-like primitive collections, leading to them becoming sparse in population without method of copulating. Self destructive in nature, although powerful.</p>
<p>The story is set around 2 people, a man and woman. They are happy to have each other around in this apocalypse, they survive for months through continuous hardship fighting/avoiding these beings. But the man is becoming more and more tired, he figures that life will never become better, every second of every single day at every inconvenience he just wants it to be over. To him, this could be a tempory problem, but what if it never gets better? What is the point of living through this? Everyday involves pain with no reward in sight. The man decides to give himself to one of the hunters right in front of the woman.</p>
<p>so there's 2 ways this ends, tell me which one sounds better:<br />
a) the woman is depressed for a while but then recovers stronger from the death of her friend, moving past it and continues with the hope of a better future</p>
<p>b) the woman is completely broken by the death of her friend and falls into a depression adopting the hopelessness of the man and is mauled by the hunters</p>
<p>I also have an alternate setting: humanity is obliterated, there is barely anyone still living. The man and woman are alone and that sense of loneliness without hope of a better future. The man, living with depression since he was very young only has it amplified in this bleak setting and he dies, not from monsters but by his own volition.</p>
<p>Which leaves the woman alone, without anyone left alive. The only person who kept her company dies from something completely out of her control.<br />
a) she keeps going and finds someone else<br />
b) she never finds anyone else and continues surviving by herself in a castaway situation in the company of a backpack with a face drawn on it.</p>
<p><strong>Hook/Attention-Grabber:</strong> The end of the world scenario in of itself as a starting point and the interesting relationship between these two in this new world would be a good way to introduce the story. Their daily lives and their battles and the like, before arriving at the climax to make it impactful.</p>
<p>thank you for reviewing my idea! I know it has a lot of problems but I'm happy to hear feedback.</p>
</div>
</div>
